    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Divination by means of signs derived from configurations of earth, such as from a handful of earth thrown upon a surface, or from arrangements of dots jotted down on paper at random. It was popular throughout Africa and Europe in the Middle Ages and the Renaissance.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Adivinación por los significados de los signos derivados de configuraciones de tierra, así como de un puñado de tierra arrojado sobre una superficie o de dispocisiones de puntos anotados en un papel al azar.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Voorspelling aan de hand van tekens die zijn ontleend aan configuraties van aarde, zoals van een handje aarde dat op een oppervlak wordt gegooid of van de rangschikking van stippen die willekeurig op papier zijn gezet.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
